# React Patterns

## Composition over props

- Components consume context directly via hooks — no deep prop chains
- State lives in contexts: `NewsFeedContext`, `GeminiSummaryContext`, `ThemeContext`
- Each context exposes a `useXxx()` hook (e.g. `useNewsFeed()`)

## Component rules

- Functional components only (no class components)
- No data transformation logic in components — delegate to utils or hooks
- Custom hooks for any reusable or complex logic (sentiment counts, period filtering, etc.)
- Hooks grouped by domain in `hooks/` folder, one file per logical grouping

## Error handling

- Services return `{ data, error: AppError | null }` result objects
- Components render `<ErrorDisplay>` for errors — full or compact variant
- Factory functions create typed errors: `createNetworkError()`, `createApiError()`, etc.
